rComments: I understand C so well because of her
Made the CSC443 material so clear and awesome. Thank you!!
GREAT EXPERIENCE !!!! I wish she would teach me class for CSC369 ! I understand C so well now .

Underrated lecturer. At the end of the course had a great understanding. Good lecture slides. Great personality. Answers random technical questions well on the spot in class. Funny. Hard working. Keep up the good work Marina!

helped me in office hours so much! i had problems with recursive C functions and she showed me all i needed to know. didnt learn this stuff well in 148 but marina was there helping me every step of the way. best prof ever
The greatest professor I've had at UofT. Only in my second year but I've taken 3 courses with her because she's really amazing. Highly recommended!
One of the best professors I have had at the University of Toronto.  Great professor!!!!!
She has a way of making every lecture entertaining. She speaks so eloquently her words become embedded in ones mind.

No other professors at the University of Toronto even comes close to this individual. She exudes kindness and care for her students, incorporating their feedback into future lectures and learns from students weak points.  I recommend taking any course with her, as it will both help you become a better Computer Scientist and a better student.
Honestly the best professor i've ever had in my life and I'm in my 8th year.
All CS professors should be as kind and funny as Marina. Has helped me a ton with c during office hours!
Marina changed my view of the world. She gets such a unique reaction from students; it's inspirational.

Marina Barsky is one of the best professors (and she's Slavic, what a benefit)!  She has clear assignments with little mistakes, clear lectures, and is super helpful during office hours. This is an easy A if you put in the effort.
